gobblin.data.management.conversion.hive.source

Class HiveSource

  • java.lang.Object
    • gobblin.data.management.conversion.hive.source.HiveSource
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Source
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    HiveAvroToOrcSource

    @Alpha
public class HiveSource
extends Object
implements Source

    A Source that creates generic workunits for a hive table or a hive partition.

    • It uses the HiveDatasetFinder to find all hive tables and partitions
    • The update time of a hive Table or a hive Partition if found using HiveUnitUpdateProvider
    • The update time from the previous run is used as previous hive watermark.HiveSourceWatermarker is used to get previous hive watermarks
    WorkUnits are created if the previous high watermark of a Partition or a Table are lower than the latest update time.

    The WorkUnits contain a serialized json of the SerializableHiveTable or SerializableHivePartition This is later deserialized by the extractor.

      • HIVE_SOURCE_IGNORE_DATA_PATH_IDENTIFIER_KEY

        public static final String HIVE_SOURCE_IGNORE_DATA_PATH_IDENTIFIER_KEY
        Comma separated list of keywords to look for in path of table (in non-partitioned case) / partition (in partitioned case) and if the keyword is found then ignore the table / partition from processing. This is useful in scenarios like: - when the user wants to ignore hourly partitions and only process daily partitions and only way to identify that is by the path both store there data. eg: /foo/bar/2016/12/01/hourly/00 - when the user wants to ignore partitions that refer to partitions pointing to /tmp location (for debug reasons)
        See Also:
